            <h2>Objectives</h2>
            <ol>
                <li><b>API</b> integration</li>
                <li><b>Express.js</b> and <b>Node.js</b> (server side programming.) </li>
                <li>Implementation of <b>CRUD </b>forms.</li>
                <li><b>PostgreSQL</b> data base</li> 
            </ol>

            <h3>Technical details</h3>
            <p>With the objectives set, these are the modules that my Book Notes project integrates to accomplish the result.</p>

            <ul>
                <li>express</li>
                <li>body-parser</li>
                <li>pg</li>
                <li>axios</li>
            </ul>

            <p>In addition to this, a PosgreSQL database was created to hold the tables needed to store the projects data.</p>

            <p>Lastly, for the API integration, I used the<u><a href="https://openlibrary.org/dev/docs/api/covers">Open Library Covers API</a></u> to <b>automatically fetch</b> book covers, based on <b>title</b> and <b>author</b>.</p>
            <ol>
